title: Election for Consiglio Grande e Generale (Sammarinese Grand and General Council)
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - At Stake in this Election: 




All 60 seats on the Sammarinese Grand and General Council 




Government Structure:  




Chief of State: Captains Regent Alessandro ROSSI and Milena GASPERONI (since 1 April 2024) 






Head of Government: N/A 






Assembly: unicameral Grand and General Council (Consiglio Grande e Generale) with 60 seats 




Electoral System:  




The Captains Regent are indirectly elected by the Grand and General Council and serve a 6-month term. There is no absolute term limit, but Captains Regent must not serve an additional term within three years of the prior term. 






All 60 members of the Grand and General Council are directly elected by list proportional representation vote in up to two rounds. All members serve unlimited 5-year terms. 




Last Election: 


In the 2019 legislative election, the San Marino Christian Democratic Party (PDCS) won the largest share of seats (21 out of 60) followed by five additional parties. Voter turnout was 55.73%. 


Information for Voters: 


Come si vota / How to vote (in Italian) 


Key Deadlines: 




Candidate filing deadline: varies by affiliation 








30 April for coalitions 






4 May for political parties not participating in coalitions 






Voter registration deadline: N/A; Voter registration is passive and residence-based. 




Main Parties in this Election: 




Libera/PS – PSD 






Coalition made up of Libera/PS and PSD 






Leader: Dalibor RICCARDI 






Seats won in last election: 18 out of 60 (10 Libera and 8 PS-PSD) 






Democracy and Liberty / Democrazia e Libertà  






Coalition made up of PDCS and Alleanza Riformista 






Leader: Gian Carlo VENTURINI and  






Seats won in last election: 21 out of 60 (all PDCS) 






Supportive Democracy / Democrazia Solidale (Demos) 






Leader: Carlo BOFFA 






Seats won in last election: 0 out of 60 (new party) 






Future Republic / Repubblica Futura (RF) 






Leader: Roberto GIORGETTI 






Seats won in last election: 6 out of 60 






Tomorrow – Free Movement / Domani – Motus Liberi (DML) 








Leader: Lorenzo Forcellini REFFI 






Seats won in last election: 4 out of 60 






RETE Civic Movement / Movimento Civico RETE 






Leader: Emanuele SANTI 






Seats won in last election: 11 out of 60 




Population and Registered Voters: 




Population: 33,660 (2022 est.) 






Registered Voters: 38,642 (2024) 




Gender Data: 




Female Population: 17,280 (2022 est.) 






CEDAW Status: Signed 26 September 2003, Ratified 10 December 2003 






Gender Quota: On each party or coalition list, candidates of the same gender may not take up more than two-thirds of list entries (Legge 31 gennaio 1996 no. 6, Art. 15.1). 






Female Candidates in this election: Yes 






Number of Female Legislators (pre-election): 20 out of 60 (33.3%) in the Grand and General Council   






Human Development Index (HDI) Position: 0.867, Very High, Rank 43 (2022) 






Social Institutions and Gender Index (SIGI) Categorization: Not available  




Disability Data: 






CRPD Status: Signed 30 March 2007, Ratified 22 February 2008 






Projected population with a disability: 5,386 (2022 est.)

Does IFES have a presence in San Marino: No 






Election Access: Yes
